Insert Logo and Title 11

Step 1. Add the Colaberry Logo

Steps

  1. From the homepage of Power BI Desktop click on the Insert tab.
  2. Click on the Image button.
  3. Browse to the location where you saved the Zip file you downloaded for this project and select the Colaberry Logo file.
  4. Click the Open button as shown in the Step 4 above.


Step 2. Adjust the canvas size


Steps

To adjust the size of the canvas click on an empty space in the canvas and follow the following steps.

  1. Click the Format pane to display the formatting options.
  2. Go to the Page Size option.
  3. Go to Type and select Custom from the drop down menu.
  4. Set the Width to 1483.
  5. Set the height to 1000

Step 3. Adjust the page background


Steps

To the background of the dashboard click on  an empty space in the canvas and follow the following steps.

  1. Click on the Format Pane and expand the Page Background tab.
  2. Set the color to Hexadecimal CCCCCC and Transparency to 53% as shown in the image above.


Step 4. Resize the Logo


Steps

To adjust the size of the Colaberry logo, click the logo image inserted into the canvas and follow the following steps.

  1. Click on the General tab in the Format Image Pane.
  2. Set the X  Position to 0.
  3. Set the Y Position to 0.
  4. Set the Width to 144.
  5. Set the height to 144.

Step 5. Create the Title


Steps

To create title for the dashboard click on  an empty space in the canvas and follow the following steps.

  1. Click on the Insert tab from the home page of Power BI Desktop.
  2. Click on the Text Box button.
  3. Select Font Size 24, Bold, Font Color White and type the title in the text box.
  4. Select the Text Box and turn the Background On in the Visualization Pane.
  5. Expand the Background tab and select the drop down color picker. Click on Custom Color and enter Hexadecimal  007FFF             

Step 6. Adjust the size and location of the title in the dashboard

Steps

To adjust the size and location of the title visual click on the title Text Box and follow the following steps.

  1. Click on the General tab in the Visualizations Pane ti expand it.
  2. Set the X  Position to 144
  3. Set the Y Position to 0.
  4. Set the Width to 369
  5. Set the height to 144.

You will get the following result.


Step 7. Turn the visual shadow on


Steps

In this step we will turn the visual shadow on to make it standout against the background.

  1. Click on the Visual.
  2. Go to Format Pane and turn the shadow on as shown in the image above.

This is a youtube video how to use custom icons and logos on our dashboard.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bH17uRRwaJA
